parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The cracking and disintegration of the dashboard can cause sharp plastic projectiles to fly out, potentially injuring occupants, and obstructing the driver's view, leading to accidents. Additionally, the broken pieces can fall into the air vents, causing electrical problems and potentially leading to fires.
symptoms: pieces of plastic breaking off and falling into the air vents
pieces flying out when the air conditioner or defroster is turned on
and potential for airbag deployment to send plastic shards into the air.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion of the frame can cause structural damage, leading to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: particularly on the left-hand side of the vehicle
just under the driver-side aft door
corrosion eating away at the bottom and sides of the frame
frame hanging on by a small piece of metal.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the pinion nut can cause the drive shaft to fall off, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
The failure of the rear axle can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries.
The failure of the drive shaft can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries.
The failure of the clutch can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: Clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
clutch pedal sticks to the floor
clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position.
